COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 477, L.D. 1145
415 park owner intends to accept, the requirements of this section apply separately to each
426 subsequent offer.
3 Sec. 3. 10 MRSA §9094-A, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
4 6. Assignment of rights. A group of mobile home owners or a mobile home owners'
5 association that has rights under this section may, upon a majority vote, assign those rights
6 to the following entities as long as the entity agrees to continue operating the property as a
7 mobile home park:
8 A. The municipality in which the mobile home park is located;
9 B. The Maine State Housing Authority or a municipal housing authority established
10 under Title 30-A, section 4721 whose area of operation, as defined in Title 30-A,
11 section 4702, subsection 1, includes the municipality in which the mobile home park
12 is located; or
13 C. A nonprofit organization.'
14 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
15 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
16 takes effect when approved.'
17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, as described below, is
2211 identical to the majority report except that the minority report requires the terms and
2222 conditions of a competing offer from a group of mobile home owners or a mobile home
2233 owners' association to be equal or superior to the terms and conditions of an offer the mobile
2244 home park owner intends to accept.
25 The amendment adds an emergency preamble and emergency clause to the bill. It
26 retains the current law that a group of mobile home owners or a mobile home owners'
27 association has 60 days within which to make an offer to a mobile home park owner to
28 purchase the mobile home park currently on the market or for which the park owner has
29 received a purchase offer the park owner intends to accept. It also adds or clarifies the
30 following:
31 1. If the offer from a group of mobile home owners or a mobile home owners'
32 association is at the same price and equal or superior terms and conditions as an offer the
33 mobile home park owner intends to accept, the group of mobile home owners or the mobile
34 home owners' association has the first option to purchase the park;
35 2. A group of mobile home owners or a mobile home owners' association has 90 days
36 after the execution of a purchase and sale agreement with the mobile home park owner
37 within which to secure appropriate financing;
38 3. The purchase and sale of a mobile home park must occur within a commercially
39 reasonable time after the receipt of the commitment for appropriate financing;
Page 4 - 132LR1672(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 477, L.D. 1145
1 4. If a group of mobile home owners or a mobile home owners' association fails to get
2 financing within the 90-day period or fails to close within a commercially reasonable time,
3 the mobile home park owner has no further obligations with respect to the proposed sale;
4 5. A mobile home park owner may not reject an offer from a group of mobile home
5 owners or a mobile home owners' association solely on the basis that the offer includes a
6 financing contingency;
7 6. The obligation to provide notice and consider an offer from a group of mobile home
8 owners or a mobile home owners' association applies if the mobile home park owner offers
9 the park for sale or intends to accept an offer to purchase the park at a different price or
10 different terms and conditions; and
11 7. The Maine State Housing Authority, a municipal housing authority, a municipality
12 where the park is located or a nonprofit organization may be assigned the first option to
13 purchase provided to the mobile home owners under the bill.
